{{Infobox Theatre |name = Aleksandër Moisiu Theatre |image = Sheshi Liria, Durrës, Shqipëri 10.jpg |caption = Aleksandër Moisiu Theatre |address = Lagja Nr: 2, Square Liria |city = [[Durrës]] |country = {{flag|Albania}} |designation = |coordinates = {{coord|41.3143|19.4465|type:landmark|display=inline}} |architect = |owner = State owned |capacity = |type = |opened = 11 January 1953 |yearsactive = |rebuilt = |closed = |othernames = Teatri i Durrësit |production = |currentuse = |website = }} [[File:Aleksandër Moisiu Theatre Durrës 1978.jpg|thumb|Theatre in 1978]] The '''Aleksandër Moisiu Theatre''', or called also '''Durrës Theatre''' ({{lang-sq|Teatri Aleksandër Moisiu}}) is a theatre in the city centre of [[Durrës]], [[Albania]]. The theatre took its name from Austrian actor [[Alexander Moissi]], who was of Albanian descent.
==History== The building of the theatre dates from the 1950s. It officially opened on January 11, 1953.<ref>[http://lajme.shqiperia.com/lajme/artikull/iden/386899/titulli/Teatri-Aleksander-Moisiu-feston-57-vjetorin-me-shfaqjen-Ana-Kristi Teatri Aleksandër Moisiu feston 57 vjetorin, me shfaqjen Ana Kristi], Lajme Shqipëria, 2010-10-07 (in Albanian)</ref> His first show was the comedy "The Girl from the village" ({{lang-sq|Vajza nga fshati}}) the writer Fatmir Gjata, staged by director Pandi Stillu.<ref>[http://www.balkanweb.com/kultur%C3%AB/2691/teatri-aleksander-moisiu-pergatitet-per-jubileun-e-60-te-78743.html Teatri "Aleksandër Moisiu" përgatitet për jubileun e 60-të], balkanweb, 2012-01-12 (in Albania)</ref>
