'''Quazal Technologies Inc.''' (formerly '''Proksim Software Inc.'''), [[doing business as]] '''Quazal''' (formerly '''Proksim Software'''), is a Canadian [[software developer]] based in [[Montreal]], [[Quebec]]. Founded in 1997 by Sylvain Beaudry, Martin Lavoie and Carl Dionne, the company focuses on the development of [[cross-platform]] [[Multiplayer video game|multiplayer]] tools for [[video game]]s, most notably, Net-Z and Rendez-Vous.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.gamasutra.com/view/feature/130572/middleware_postmortem_quazal_.php |title=Middleware Postmortem: Quazal Technologies |last=Drummelsmith |first=Mike |date=8 November 2004 |website=[[Gamasutra]] |publisher=[[UBM TechWeb]] |accessdate=1 May 2017}}</ref> On 4 November 2010, it was announced that [[Ubisoft]] had acquired Quazal.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.gamesindustry.biz/articles/2010-11-05-ubisoft-acquires-long-term-partner-quazal |title=Ubisoft acquires long-term partner Quazal |last=Pearson |first=Dan |date=5 November 2010 |website=[[GamesIndustry.biz]] |publisher=[[Gamer Network]] |accessdate=1 May 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.gameinformer.com/b/news/archive/2010/11/04/ubisoft-acquires-multiplayer-middleware-company.aspx |title=Ubisoft Acquires Multiplayer Middleware Company |last=Bertz |first=Matt |date=4 November 2010 |website=[[Game Informer]] |publisher=[[GameStop]] |accessdate=1 May 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.ign.com/articles/2010/11/04/ubisoft-acquires-quazal-technologies |title=Ubisoft Acquires Quazal Technologies |author=IGN Staff |date=4 November 2010 |website=[[IGN]] |publisher=[[IGN Entertainment]] |accessdate=1 May 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.gamasutra.com/view/news/122020/Ubisoft_Bolsters_Online_Services_With_Quazal_Acquisition.php |title=Ubisoft Bolsters Online Services With Quazal Acquisition |last=Leigh |first=Alexander |date=4 November 2010 |website=[[Gamasutra]] |publisher=[[UBM TechWeb]] |accessdate=1 May 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gamasutra.com/view/news/91377/Proksim_Announces_NetZ_for_PlayStation_2.php|title=Gamasutra - The Art & Business of Making Games|author=|date=|website=www.gamasutra.com|accessdate=27 May 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.engadget.com/2009/03/22/quazal-inks-middleware-deal-with-ubisoft-petz-deathmatch-now-po/|title=Quazal inks middleware deal with Ubisoft, Petz deathmatch now possible|author=|date=|website=Engadget|accessdate=27 May 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gamasutra.com/view/news/19262/Quazal_Multiplayer_Tech_Integrated_Into_Vision_Engine_7.php|title=Gamasutra - The Art & Business of Making Games|first=|last=Staff|date=|website=www.gamasutra.com|accessdate=27 May 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ign.com/articles/2004/06/16/splinter-cell-3-goes-online-with-quazal|title=Splinter Cell 3 Goes Online with Quazal|first=Juan|last=Castro|date=16 June 2004|website=ign.com|accessdate=27 May 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gameplanet.co.nz/news/i127248/PlayStation-online-middleware-gets-approval-from-Sony/|title=PlayStation online middleware gets approval from Sony|author=|date=|website=gameplanet.co.nz|accessdate=27 May 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.pcgamer.com/relic-to-continue-supporting-company-of-heroes-online-servers-moving-to-steamworks/|title=Relic to continue supporting Company of Heroes' online, servers moving to Steamworks|author=|date=|website=pcgamer.com|accessdate=27 May 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.polygon.com/2013/4/22/4252504/company-of-heroes-migrating-to-steamworks-may-7-original-servers|title=Company of Heroes migrating to Steamworks May 7, original servers shutting down|author=|date=22 April 2013|website=Polygon|accessdate=27 May 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gamezone.com/originals/quazal-39-s-psp-middleware-approved|title=Quazal's PSP Middleware Approved|first=|last=GameZone|date=|website=gamezone.com|accessdate=27 May 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gamesindustry.biz/articles/add-a-spark-to-your-online-development|title=Add a Spark to your Online Development!|author=|date=|website=gamesindustry.biz|accessdate=27 May 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gamesindustry.biz/articles/quazal-trinigy-deal-online-tech-incorporated-into-vision-engine|title=Quazal/Trinigy deal|author=|date=|website=gamesindustry.biz|accessdate=27 May 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gamesindustry.biz/articles/2014-05-12-ea-confirms-50-games-going-offline|title=EA confirms 50 games going offline|author=|date=|website=gamesindustry.biz|accessdate=27 May 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gamesindustry.biz/articles/eidos-signs-up-quazal-for-console-online-titles|title=Eidos signs up Quazal for console online titles|author=|date=|website=gamesindustry.biz|accessdate=27 May 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gamesindustry.biz/articles/quazal-releases-net-z-43-and-rendez-vous-20|title=Quazal Releases Net-Z 4.3 and Rendez-Vous 2.0|author=|date=|website=gamesindustry.biz|accessdate=27 May 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gamasutra.com/view/news/97621/Quazal_Announces_NetZ_RendezVous_For_Xbox_360.php|title=Gamasutra - The Art & Business of Making Games|first=Simon|last=Carless|date=|website=www.gamasutra.com|accessdate=27 May 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gamasutra.com/view/news/97850/Eidos_Uses_Quazal_Tech_for_Commandos.php|title=Gamasutra - The Art & Business of Making Games|first=Nich|last=Maragos|date=|website=www.gamasutra.com|accessdate=27 May 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gamesindustry.biz/articles/quazal-rocks-out-with-harmonix-and-rock-band|title=Quazal Rocks Out with Harmonix and Rock Band™!|author=|date=|website=gamesindustry.biz|accessdate=27 May 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gamesindustry.biz/articles/quazal-update-net-z--rendez-vous-and-spark--get-support-for-iphone--wii-and-games-for-windows-live|title=Quazal update|author=|date=|website=