{{Culture of Turkey}}
The '''[[theatre]] of [[Turkey]]''' encompasses the traditional theatre practice of the [[Ottoman Empire|Ottoman]] period and the modern Turkish theatre. In Turkey, theatre acts are performed by numerous private theatre companies and subsidized companies such as the general directorate of [[Turkish State Theatres]] or Istanbul Municipality Theatre.

==History==
The [[Darülbedayi]] was an Ottoman imperial theatre established in Istanbul in 1914 and run by the actor [[Muhsin Ertuğrul]].<ref>The Turkish muse: views & reviews, 1960s-1990s - Page 252 Talât Sait Halman, Jayne L. Warner - 2006 "His emphasis is less on the artistic evolution of the Darulbedayi than on its organizational and structural growth. To a large extent, the history of this remarkable repertory theater is dominated by Muhsin Ertugrul as artistic director, actor, ..."</ref>

