{{Infobox roller coaster |name=Trailblazer |image= Trailblazer sign.jpg <!--Use ONLY the filename, not a full [[Image:]] link--> |caption= Trailblazer's entrance |location=Hersheypark <!--Must not be linked, will auto-categorize the coaster.--> |section=Pioneer Frontier <!--Must not be linked.--> |type=Steel <!--Must be "Steel" or "Wood", nothing else. Must not be linked.--> |type2= <!--Must not be linked, will auto-categorize the coaster.--> |type3= <!--Must not be linked, will auto-categorize the coaster.--> |status=Operating |opened=1974 |manufacturer=Arrow Development <!--Must not be linked, will auto-categorize the coaster.--> |designer= |model=Mine train |track= |lift=Chain [[lift hill]] |height_ft=43 |drop_ft= <!--Must be expressed in feet and may contain only numeric characters.--> |length_ft=1600 <!--Must be expressed in feet and may contain only numeric characters.--> |speed_mph=35 <!--Must be expressed in miles per hour and may contain only numeric characters.--> |inversions=0 |duration=1:15 |angle= <!--Do not include "degrees", it is added automatically.--> |capacity=1125 |cost= |acceleration= |gforce= |restriction_in=36 <!--Must be expressed in inches and may contain only numeric characters.--> |rcdb_number=107 <!--The number in the URL of the coaster's RCDB page--> |coordinates={{Coord|40.289172|-76.653478|display=it}} }} '''Trailblazer''' is a [[family roller coaster]] at [[Hersheypark]] [[amusement park]] in [[Hershey, Pennsylvania|Hershey]], [[Pennsylvania]]. It is located in the Pioneer Frontier section of Hersheypark, just below Storm Runner. The ride is notable for being the second-oldest operating coaster in the park, after the [[Comet (Hersheypark)|Comet]], and for its family-friendly height requirement of 36&nbsp;inches and above with an adult.
==Description== The coaster reaches speeds of up to 45&nbsp;mph, and features a helix that circles 4 times. The mid-course brake zone is nearly level with [[Storm Runner]], and the queue for that ride extends inside Trailblazer's first drop.
==History== According to a 1974 Souvenir book printed before the coaster was finalized, the ride was supposed to feature two lifts.<ref>Hershey's Guidebook, Western Publishing Company, 1974.</ref>
The ride received two brand new trains in 2003 built by [[Premier Rides]]. The main difference is the new cars had individual lap bars for each seat, rather than the single "t-bar" lap bars for each pair of seats.
